Vladimir Putin discussed with the chairman of the Defenders of the Fatherland Foundation, Anna Tsivileva, issues of supporting the participants in the special operation and their families. The Russian leader held a working meeting with the head of the Defenders of the Fatherland Foundation, Anna Tsivileva. During it, Putin promised to make a decision to extend the procedure for assigning the status of a combat disabled person to PMC employees. Other statements from the working conversation:

— The President agreed to provide seriously wounded SVO participants who lost both legs with manually controlled cars;

— 12 thousand volunteers received certificates of combat veterans;

— The Defenders of the Fatherland Foundation has processed 910 thousand requests over 10 months of work, of which 780 thousand have already been resolved.

